---
/* =============================================================================
   SKIP LINK — Accessibility skip-to-content link (WCAG 2.1 requirement)
   =============================================================================
   This hidden link becomes visible when a keyboard user presses Tab on page
   load. It jumps focus directly to the <main id="main-content"> element,
   skipping the navigation. Every page includes this via BaseLayout.

   How it works on the webpage:
   - Invisible by default (positioned off-screen with .sr-only styles)
   - On :focus (Tab key), it slides into view at the top of the page
   - Clicking it moves focus to #main-content, skipping the nav bar

   Future improvement: Add smooth scroll behavior if desired.

   Coordinated changes:
   - Used by: BaseLayout.astro (first element on every page)
   - If you change the target id → update BaseLayout main element id to match
   ============================================================================= */
---

<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">
  Skip to main content
</a>

<style>
  /* Visually hidden until focused — uses the .sr-only pattern but overrides
     on :focus to make it visible and prominent at the top of the page */
  .skip-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -100%;
    left: var(--space-2);
    z-index: 1000;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: top 0.15s ease;
  }

  /* When the user tabs to this link, slide it into view */
  .skip-link:focus {
    top: var(--space-1);
    outline: 2px solid var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
